        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer190897219" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14105755117628527979">My husband read this book shortly after receiving a stage-4 terminal diagnosis. It was a huge help to him in resolving his feelings and being able to be &quot;in the moment&quot; and I&apos;m grateful that I could be &quot;in the moment&quot; with him. I have since read this book myself and corny as it sounds, it&apos;s not a book about dying, it&apos;s a book about how to go about living. No regrets here, your life is what you can make of it.</span>
  <span id="freeText14105755117628527979" style="display:none">My husband read this book shortly after receiving a stage-4 terminal diagnosis. It was a huge help to him in resolving his feelings and being able to be "in the moment" and I'm grateful that I could be "in the moment" with him. I have since read this book myself and corny as it sounds, it's not a book about dying, it's a book about how to go about living. No regrets here, your life is what you can make of it.</span>
