  <span id="freeText18102763223254669907" style="display:none">An very touching, inspiring, and difficult book to read. Written almost totally by Gene O'Kelly, this book is a story about his own personal "winding down" of his life after finding out he had cancer in May of 2005. He passed in September of 2005 (I believe I have the dates right). While certainly moving, the provides new insight into a person who was given the opportunity to actively bring their life to a close.<br /><br />Instructive and poingant, there book is full of lessons we should be applying every day.</span>
